.TH "rvt_modify_qp" 9 "rvt_modify_qp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_modify_qp \- modify the attributes of a queue pair
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rvt_modify_qp
.BI "(struct ib_qp *ibqp "  ","
.BI "struct ib_qp_attr *attr "  ","
.BI "int attr_mask "  ","
.BI "struct ib_udata *udata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ibqp" 12
the queue pair who's attributes we're modifying
.IP "attr" 12
the new attributes
.IP "attr_mask" 12
the mask of attributes to modify
.IP "udata" 12
user data for libibverbs.so
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, otherwise returns an errno.
